<br />
While I am sure this is fine advice, it is also totally worthless, because A)  If I'm charm soloing, I don't have room to load Color Cloud - and WoM is superior 90% of the time. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">I have to disagree with this.  CC is much better if you are trying to time it such that you can kill your pet in one nuke for full exp and get another pet.  That is something that I can see done literally as often as you cast CoD while charm soloing.  All you have to do is run in and stun the target so it won't damage your pet once your pet hits Nuke range.  More than likely you can even use this to get the target to nuke range as well.  Then you can Mez, Invis, Root, Nuke, Nuke and move on.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">B) If I'm not charm soloing, I'm unlikely to be in an area where I have room to run to max spell range and still maintain line of sight, and </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">Thing is that you *don't* have to run until max spell range.  You just have to run only when your gems are gray from the casting of Color Cloud.  Whenever I have a former pet get unstunned early and break my concentration on the CoD it was literally in the last few iotas of my cast time.  You don't need full spell range.  You just need to be out of reach for the space of those few iotas.  I'm pretty sure that the situations where you can't run in a straight line for the time it takes your spell gems to refresh are few and far between.  Now all you have to do is hope that you fully stopped moving before you started casting...  
<br />

