                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Unmei wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">This sadly does nothing to change the fact that WoM is better for recharms and that I only have room for one of these spells.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">I'm not debating that.  You were saying that it was better for charm soloing.  There are two major ways this is done.  One is with a constant pet and the other is with a new pet for every two mobs.  If you are recharming WoM is better because it's a half second faster casting and they last for about the same amount of time.  If you are not recharming, you will want Color Cloud because it allows you to have an AE up in the unlikely case that charm breaks before they die or in the case that you need to even up the HP of the two mobs you want to nuke.
<br />

<br />
I'm also not debating which method is better in terms of experience or safety.  It's just that both methods are viable (and IMHO are helped by different spells) and used by various people.  I dont' know what method you use when you charm solo, mostly because I'm not, well, there.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" />
