                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wish I understood how root works, but I don't.  The higher level ones for all caster classes get the -30 resist adjust, of course, but that seems to apply to initial landing.  Like some other spells, root seems to make a resist check every tick; my observation is that the root and earth lines of spells fail this secondary check more often than fetter does, for instance.  The druid/wizard AAs also make a difference, but presumably for other reasons.
