                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've never noticed any of the -30 resist mod roots breaking any earlier than any of the others.
<br />

<br />
Though an important thing to know about root is that everything a rooted creature is hit by a DD (Be it cast, procced, or whatever) - i.e. if you see that "X has hit rooted mob Y for 100 pts of non-melee damage" that creature gets another chance to break root.  So if you're got three melees with proccing weapons, a wizard, and a beastlord pet beating on a rooted mob, that root is going to last about 0.314159 seconds, regardless of the resist mod.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
