                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">since mezz mastery i neve ever considered using color cloud for recharming again
<br />

<br />
its just sooo easy to mezz the mob for 12 secs, get a quick malosini a tash and charm off before mob awakes and everthing is fine.
<br />

<br />
cc has more resists.
<br />
with cc you have to run away due the short stun time, not only you look like a newb while doing it you are most likely oor for heals, oor for crowd control and oor for slow.
<br />
using cc is always a close thing there are several circumstances where it fails, line of sight, tight quarters and even lag can make you cry this is only for charm if u want to retash/remalo you even have to mezz the pet for a minute.
<br />

<br />
someone said stun the target when it heals or gates? well with a charm pet the mobs are dead before they get gate off. if not? let the cleric stun or pally or just let him gate and deal with the adds, cant think of one gating mob while my pet was beating on it and if u dont have a pet you of course have cc memmend <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />
pet doted? duuuh thats bad but never had it doted and if u watch ur pets buffs(dots) get a quick cure <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />
problems with multi incs? well iam sorry but i stopped using pbaestun for stopping multi incs since i fought me first 500 hitter. almost everyone in your group have more ac/hp than you, if not hes a) not on the same equip level or b) disposable so why agroing everything on you? let them beat on the rangers, beastlords, shamns or even clerics.
