                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One thing is different between WoM and Color Cloud..
<br />

<br />
Aggro.
<br />

<br />
WoM = High aggro.  Color Cloud = Low aggro.
<br />

<br />
I use both rather extensively for different purposes.  WoM seems to last a bit longer than CC (though they are both registered for same time on 'em) but WoM = almost guaranteed aggro in most situations whereas CC = almost no aggro.
<br />

<br />
Mob is pulled, Mez it, Tash it, Slow it.  MT comes at it and breaks mez.  I have high aggro so... Color Cloud, step back and, by the time MoB is free to fight again, tank has aggro on them.  This works.
<br />

<br />
WoM issue today -- SolRo raid...  I hit WoM vs CC on accident with some sun MOB's heading for Jiva...  the second it landed I knew I was dead..  MT woke it instantly and it turned and beat on me -- before I could do more than pop Eldritch rune, I the other 2 were awake and on me too...
<br />

<br />
I'd used Color Cloud in that situation 5 previous pulls (2+ mobs) and hadn't been gotten at that way but 1 use of WoM...
<br />

<br />
I've had 1 of 4 jump me for using Color Cloud on a pull while 3 went after other folks.  With WoM -- I'll get all the aggro when it goes.
<br />

<br />
Resist wise -- they're about even and use wise -- depends on where you're at and what you're fighting.  In LDoN, most mobs can be mez'd AND stunned so it's fairly a toss up on which to use.   Just depends on how much aggro you are comfortable with.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
